Certainly! If you're looking for online code editors where you don't have to sign up, there are several options available. Here are a few:

1. **CodePen**: While CodePen does offer a sign-up option for additional features, you can also use it without signing up. Just visit the website and start coding right away. However, signing up provides benefits like saving your work.
   Website: [CodePen](https://codepen.io/)

2. **JSFiddle**: Similar to CodePen, JSFiddle allows you to write and test code without signing up. You can use it immediately to experiment with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
   Website: [JSFiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/)

3. **JS Bin**: JS Bin also offers a no-sign-up option for quickly testing JavaScript, HTML, and CSS code. Just visit the website and start coding in the provided editor.
   Website: [JS Bin](https://jsbin.com/)

4. **Replit**: While Replit does encourage signing up for additional features and project management, you can still use it without signing up. Just click on "Start coding now" to create a new project.
   Website: [Replit](https://replit.com/)

These platforms allow you to write and test your JavaScript code online without the need for signing up. They provide convenient environments for experimenting with code and sharing your creations.